Name: Lucy
Story: Best child ever!

Name: Oreo
Story: Oreo was found outside as a young adult. She has been spayed and is utd on shots and flea treatment. Our older cat does like her aggressive form of play and we would like to find her a new home.

Name: Jelly
Story: Jelly found himself at just a week old in a city shelter. After being hand raised, he is now ready to find his forever home. He is a loving, people friendly, pet friendly, happy, healthy kitten.

Name: Sweet Pickles
Story: Sweet Pickles found herself in a shelter at a week old. After being hand raised, she is a sweet loving, adventurous and curious girl seeking the perfect forever home.

Name: Gizmo
Story: Gizmo was found as a stray and brought into ACCT Philly. He is currently in a foster home w cats, dogs, and children. Gizmo is a playful sweety with especially long whiskers.

Name: Coco
Story: Coco's story with us started with our family fostering her when she was four month's  from a family member.  The conditions she lived under were neglect and abuse. We decided to keep her.

Name: Berry
Story: Berry was left at a crowded shelter when his family moved.  He was not picked for adoption due to his age.  We knew he didn't deserve to be killed just because he wasn't young.  He is so loving!

Name: Flip
Story: Flip was taken in from an acquaintance when they could no longer keep her. She does not like other cats, but LOVES affection from humans. She would love being an only cat with a cuddly person!

Name: Ruby
Story: Ruby is a gorgeous half German German Shepherd and half American German Shepherd. She DOES NOT LIKE other ANIMALS AT ALL and she is initially wary of strangers but she will warm up to new people in a controlled and nurturing environment. She is sweet and loving to the people who live in the house.

Name: Pootie
Story: Meet Pootie, a very special "Pootie-cat"! Pootie is a 12 year old female who loves to play. She was released to the shelter after her owners were moving. Pootie loves to rub against people and purr.

Name: LittleFoot
Story: LittleFoot is shy and needs some more socialization to help her become the loving cat I know she can be. She needs a semi active house that has a younger cat who she could bond and play with.

Name: Jazzy
Story: Jazzy's previous owners raised her alongside 5 children and a St. Bernard dog! When they moved, we adopted her to couple w/ our existing cat, but they didn't love each other like we hoped. But we do!

Name: Eve-E
Story: Eve-e is loving and playful. She hugs, she plays, she cuddles. She is excellent with children and will play as long as you want to. She needs a home when she will be loved and have play time.

Name: Munchkin
Story: Poor little Munchkin was brought to the shelter alone, hurt and afraid. She had surgery and recovered wonderfully in a loving foster home. She is now ready to live, love and play in her fur-ever home.

Name: Scooby
Story: My mother found these two beautiful pitties. They seem to be about 6-12 months. Very friendly once they get adjusted. They are shy at first. ACCT NOR PSPCA  wont take them due to space.

Name: Cassie
Story: Cassie is very active loves to run and jump and play. Spends a lot of the day watching out the window at all the kids playing. My 1.5 year old and her are so great together + She has never bit anyone.

Name: Snoppy
Story: My mother found these two beautiful pitties. They seem to be about 6-12 months. Very friendly once they get adjusted. They are shy at first. ACCT NOR PSPCA  wont take them die to space.

Name: Lexi
Story: Lexi is a beautiful and well-trained 11 year old  Blue Nose Pitbull who loves people and children. Lexi Is a sweet old gal in perfect health who just wants the love and attention she so deserves ❤️❤️

Name: Mama
Story: Sadly Mama's owner was diagnosed with a terminal illness.  We are trying to help rehome his little loved ones before he is unable to care for them any longer.  Mama is FIV+ which has not caused her any issues but since contagious to other cats, should be the only cat in the household.  Please contact us today to meet this lovely lady.

Name: Stella
Story: Stella needs a new home due to divorce & breed restrictions. she has lived with children since she came into our home. Because she lived in the country she needs help learning how to walk on a leash.

Name: Mabel
Story: Mabel was rescued from the parking lot of my work.  She is very affectionate and even gives kisses.  She will make a great pet for a loving family, you can tell she is happy to not be outside anymore.

Name: Jace
Story: UPDATE: Please be advised that my sweetheart Jace was adopted on 12/6 to a great family in Elkton, MD.

Name: Fluffernutter
Story: This boy is as soft and fluffy as they come! He is about 10 weeks old and will purrup a storm when getting petted. But you need to earn his trust first....such a sweetie

Name: Supermoon
Story: Super moon is a beautiful cat with extremely soft dark brown far.and gorgeous hazel eyes. She is quite shy but once she gets to know you she likes to be petted. About 10 weeks old

Name: Shadow
Story: Shadow is a sweetheart he's very lovable nd affectionate he loves to be pet nd he loves his tummy rub!😄 I hope you enjoy him as well as I did... I also feed him blue buffalo from Chewy.Com

Name: Antennna
Story: was born in my house and along with three kittens but don't have don't have any more space and I need someone to care for her and a nice family

Name: bella
Story: needs a caring family that's love cats and takes care of her please its a nice friendly cat

Name: Zoey
Story: It took a while to train her or to even touch her. She is a great dog for a family. Great with kids and she is very lovable and playful. She watch over me and my children but in a loving way.

Name: Crookshanks
Story: I've had Crookshanks since he was a kitten. He is very playful and loving. He responds to "Crookie" as we've been calling him that for a while.

Name: Rambo
Story: Rambo is one of five boys in a litter of six. Rambo is very shy and prefers the safety of laying beneath things rather than play but is not opposed to it. He is very well behaved.

Name: Garfield
Story: Garfield is one of five boys in a litter of six. He is one of the more laid back of the group but loves to play. Garfield is the prominent "top dog" of the kittens.

Name: Bentlie
Story: Bentliee , is well mannered and well trained . she loves walks she walks without a leash. And loves to do things for snacks lol good around kids and other animals . cant keep her due to my situation.

Name: Tiny Tim
Story: Tiny Tim was found as a stray. He is a sweetheart looking for a home for the holidays!

Name: Helen
Story: Helen is in foster care through ACCT Philly. Information on adoption fees can be found at www.acctphilly.org/adopt/ (or just email me!). Want more photos? Go to www.facebook.com/cathatchery/

Name: Foot-Foot
Story: Foot-Foot is in foster care through ACCT Philly. Information on adoption fees can be found at www.acctphilly.org/adopt/ (or just email me!). Want more photos? Go to www.facebook.com/cathatchery/

Name: Gallagher
Story: Gallagher came to live with me about 3 months after my 16 year old dog died. He became familiar very easily. The vet said he was about 4 or 5. He was a rescue. He loves to look out the window.

Name: Beauty
Story: Beauty lived with an older couple and lived there for a year until the wife passed away and Beauty went after a neighbors dog. She then lived with her breeder where she was abused and then i took her

Name: Zues
Story: Hes so lavable and smart and witty good vision good appetite loves to walk on grass he barks when he needs to use the bathroom

Name: Frosty
Story: Frosty was found abandoned in a garage. Her mother was feral and we aren't sure where she went, but she left Frosty behind.  Frosty is great with kids and lets them treat her like a toy!

Name: Kiya
Story: Kiya was adopted from a kill shelter approximately 7 years ago by my son's roommate before they met. Unfortunately Kiya's master moved out & left her behind. Now my son must move & cannot take her.

Name: Zoey
Story: Last year Zoey and I moved in with my parents, and despite our best efforts she and their cats could not get along. Since I can't afford to move us both, I'm looking for a loving new guardian for her.

Name: Frankie
Story: Frankie is a very loving affectionate puppy. He needs and wants a lot of attention. He is great with kids and other animals. He gets excited but calms down moments later. He loves to cuddle!

Name: Naila
Story: Naila was used as a breeding dog.  She knows sit and lay down well.  She loves cuddling and will sleep next to you all night long.  She is good with dogs just too interested in cats to live with them.

Name: Brownie
Story: Brownie is a very good loving dog she can get attached really quickly. She's a water lover, loves to play a lot, and she loves going on long walks. She can really be the best friend you never had.

Name: Cesar
Story: Cesar is a 4 year old mini poodle, who is not quite mini at slightly over 20lbs. He is energetic, house broken, and gets along with cats.  Cesar barks at strangers, but does know simple commands.

Name: April
Story: we adopted april in April of 2014 her original name at the delco SPCA was peanut. She loves to run after a lazer light and warms up after she checks you out. She meows for treats. She is a great pet.

Name: Princess
Story: Princess is an amazing, lovable, cuddly, playful girl!  She's great with children and thinks she's a big baby herself! She is timid and takes time to warm but but once she does, shes awesome!

Name: Angel
Story: Angel is a sweet great dane.  She loves people and through no fault of her own,  she needs to find a new home with people who will love her and care for her in their home.  She deserves nothing less.

Name: Eliza
Story: Eliza quickly went from a stray in my backyard to a loving friend. She adores being cuddled & pet, and purrs when she eats. She's had a tough life on the streets and deserves a great forever home.

Name: Sunny
Story: I have other animals He likes other cats because he lived with them before. He was neutered/vaccinated on12/15/16. He is sweet & will need a good home soon

Name: Sebastian
Story: Hi! My Name is Sebastian. I'm about 6 years old and love to cuddle. I'm curious, affectionate and playful. And I get along well with other cats.

Name: DeMarcus
Story: De's a loving boy who needs a home.  I took him in from outside & tried to give him a happy home.  I have 3 other strays that now are bullying him.  They take his food & fight w/him.   Please help him

Name: Prime
Story: Prime came to us as a puppy. I had only one child and couldn't afford another mouth to feed but my son loved him.  As my family has grown,  my space has shrunk and so has my free time and money.

Name: Hobbes
Story: Hobbes is a sweet puppy that is very affectionate and attached to her human. Very energetic and agile. She needs more space to run and exercise which I do not have.

Name: Ali
Story: Hi, I'm Ali. I need a new home cuz my family is losing theirs. I love to cuddle & give kisses. I don't like it outside & get nervous around other pets & new people, I really need a new family to love.

Name: Cali
Story: Hi, I'm Cali. I need a new home cuz my family is losing theirs. I love to cuddle & give kisses. I don't like it outside & get nervous around other pets & new people, I really need a new family to love

Name: TicTac
Story: TicTac is the only girl in a litter of six. She is the smallest and likes to watch whatever trouble her silly brothers get into but is always up for a little fun. Tic has beautiful hazel eyes.
